      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="0" field="7eb5-fae3-a137-546c">
          <conditionGroups>
            <conditionGroup type="and">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="2" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="cd66-a353-13f7-ee30" shared="true" childName="Blood Brothers"/>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="fcbb-50c3-5314-955a" shared="true" childName="Priest of Taal"/>
              </conditions>
            </conditionGroup>
          </conditionGroups>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <rules>
        <rule name="Loner" id="60c6-ce2a-6756-d927" hidden="false">
          <description>Few people care to spend any length of time in the company of a priest of Morr - even when it is their duty to do so.


As such, a priest of Morr is used to being alone and probably prefers it that way. 


Priests of Morr do not suffer from the All Alone rules.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Funerary Rites" id="ed14-1b43-3317-885b" hidden="false">
          <description>Priests of Morr are not wizards by any means, however, they do have numerous Funerary Rites, which they may perform.


As such, priests of Morr may choose a Funerary Rite listed below, using the rules for Magic on page 56 of the Mordheim hook.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
  </selectionEntries>
  <rules>
    <rule id="0057-7432-79ff-2878" name="Self Sufficient" hidden="false">
      <description>The men of Ostland have no desire to give their hard-earned gold to outsiders.
As a result they can never hire any Mercenaries except for Ogres (who are not an uncommon sight in Ostland).</description>
    </rule>
  </rules>
